{
  "stem": "26728.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But if it was pretty static, they would gets us close to the troops because we could get there quicker.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But I was going to tell you about this one-- that one battle of-- which would-- ended up being called the Battle of the Bulge, where we were stationed at Liege, Belgium.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "And we were evacuated three times in the middle of the night because this is when the Battle of the Bulge started and everything just fell apart.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "And in the middle of the night they'd load us all into trucks, and we were-- we couldn't-- we couldn't fly.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "The ground-- it was just-- the fog was just zero.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And this is what gave the German such an advantage in the Battle of the Bulge-- wintertime, fog, heavy clouds.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "We couldn't fly air-to-ground support.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "So we were stuck right there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "But it was really very scary to be awakened in the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "And all you can do is-- is get-- get your B4 bag, and-- and you put on some clothes, and grab a pack of cigarettes, and get into a truck, and drive all night.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And they don't even know where they're going to take you.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "And-- and sleep.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "You-- you know, you're tired, you sleep standing up, for that matter.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "That happened to us three times.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "Then the weather cleared.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "And this was by now 1945, and my squadron was called Blue Fox Squadron.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "Our flight leader, name of Harold Snyder, Captain Harold Snyder, we were out on a patrol.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "And he saw a convoy in Belgium heading for France-- heading for Germany, trying to get out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "And there were tanks, trucks, men, horses.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "I mean, there must have been-- it was about five or six miles long.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
